Colombian Stock Movers: Ecopetrol, Isagen, Canacol Energy Rise

-- B y   A n d r e a   J a r a m i l l o
-- 
2011-03-01T21:30:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-01/colombian-stock-movers-ecopetrol-isagen-canacol-energy-rise.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4:11 p.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index rose 0.8 percent to 15,134.22, while the
Colcap Index gained 0.6 percent to 1,762.02.    Ecopetrol SA  (ECOPETL CB), Colombia’s largest oil company,
climbed 0.5 percent to 3,985 pesos. The state-controlled oil
producer said in a statement late yesterday that a rally in
crude prices and rising output pushed fourth-quarter profit up
57 percent to 2.70 trillion pesos ($1.41 billion) from 1.72
trillion pesos a year earlier.  Isagen SA (ISAGEN CB), a state-controlled power producer,
jumped 1.6 percent to 2,480 pesos. The Medellin-based company
said in a  filing  yesterday fourth-quarter profit more than
tripled to 201 billion pesos from 63.8 billion pesos a year
earlier.    Canacol Energy Ltd . (CNEC CB) rose 1.3 percent to 3,200
pesos. The Calgary-based oil company announced in a filing today
it signed three new exploration and production contracts with  Colombia ’s National Hydrocarbons Agency.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andrea Jaramillo in Bogota at 
 ajaramillo1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
